nan-s-film-hero-shelved-this-is-why-1574137-2019-07-27|title=Vijay Deverakonda as main lead in Anand Annamalai's next|work=India Today |date=27 July 2019| accessdate= 11 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cinemaexpress.com/stories/news/2019/mar/13/title-clash-between-the-films-of-sivakarthikeyan-and-vijay-devarakonda-10520.html|title= Movie title clash between Vijay Deverakonda and Siva Karthikeyan|accessdate= 11 January 2020|work=Cinema Express|date=13 March 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n|''Fighter''\n|\n|Filming\n|<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/movies/vijay-deverakonda-starts-shooting-for-puri-jagannadhs-fighter/article30606252.ece |title=Puri Jagannadh's Fighter |accessdate=10 February 2020|newspaper=The Hindu |date=20 January 2020}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==As producer==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-  style=\"background:#ccc; text-align:center;\"\n! Year\n! Film\n! Director\n! Notes\n! Ref\n|-\n| 2019\n| ''[[Meeku Maathrame Cheptha]]''\n| Shammeer Sultan\n|  Producer\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/meeku-mathrame-cheptha-teaser-vijay-deverakondas-maiden-production-sees-tharun-bhascker-as-a-lying-bloke-7301311.html|title=Meeku Mathrame Cheptha teaser: Vijay Deverakonda's maiden production sees Tharun Bhascker as a lying bloke|date=7 September 2019|website=Firstpost|language=en|access-date=16 October 2019}}</ref>\n|}\n\n== Awards and nominations ==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Year\n!Award\n!Category\n!Film\n!Result\n|-\n| | 2015\n| [[Nandi Awards]] \n|Special Jury Award - [[Telugu language|Telugu]]\n| |''[[Yevade Subramanyam]]''\n|  {{Won}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\"| 2017\n| [[Filmfare Awards South]] \n|Best Actor - [[Telugu language|Telugu]]\n| rowspan=\"3\" |''[[Arjun Reddy]]''\n| rowspan=3 {{Won}}\n|-\n| [[Zee Telugu]] Golden Awards\n|Golden Awards for Best Actor\n|-\n| Behindwoods Gold Medal \n|The South Indian Sensation\n|-\n| | 2018\n| [[Zee Telugu]] Golden Awards\n| Favourite Actor\n| rowspan=\"2\"|''[[Geetha Govindam]]''\n| {{Won}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\" |2019\n| Sri Kala Sudha Telugu Association Awards\n| Best Actor\n| {{Won}}\n|-\n| Hindustan times India's most stylish 2019 Awards\n| Hottest stylista\n|\n| {{Won}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" |[[South Indian International Movie Awards|SIIMA Film Awards]]\n|Best Actor (Critics) - Telugu\n|''[[Geetha Govindam]]''\n| {{Won}}\n|-\n|Popular Celebrity on Social Media\n|\n| {{Won}}\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons Category|Vijay Devarakonda}}\n* {{IMDb name|4797922}}\n*{{Facebook|TheDeverakonda}}\n\n{{FilmfareTeluguBestActor}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Deverakonda, Vijay}}\n[[Category:1989 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Male actors from Hyderabad, India]]\n[[Category:Telugu people]]\n[[Category:Filmfare Awards South winners]]\n[[Category:Male actors in Telugu cinema]]\n[[Category:Indian male film actors]]\n[[Category:Indian male stage actors]]\n[[Category:21st-century Indian male actors]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Indian film actor}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2019}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=February 2016}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Vijay Deverakonda \n| image              = Vijay Deverakonda at NOTA pressmeet.jpg\n| caption            = Vijay Devarakonda at ''[[NOTA (film)| NOTA]]'' press meet in 2018\n| birth_name         = Deverakonda Vijay Sai<ref>{{cite news |last1=Ravi |first1=Murali |title=Vijay Deverakonda changes his name! To what? |url=https://www.tollywood.net/vijay-deverakonda-changes-his-name-to-what/ |accessdate=2 February 2020 |work=Tollywood |date=4 January 2020}}</ref>\n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|1989|5|9|df=y}}<ref name=\"timesofindia\">{{cite news|title=Vijay Deverakonda celebrates his birth in a unique way|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/vijay-devarakonda-celebrates-his-birthday-in-a-unique-way/articleshow/64093479.cms|website=[[The Times of India]] |author=Shalini J. R. |date=9 May 2018 |accessdate=3 January 2019}}</ref>\n| birth_place        = \n| nationality        = Indian\n| alma_mater         = \n| occupation         = {{hlist|Film actor|film producer|media personality|businessperson}}\n| mother             = \n| father             = \n| family             = \n| years_active       = 2011 \u2013 present\n}}\n'''Vijay Deverakonda''' is an Indian film actor, film producer, and media personality known predominantly for his works in [[Telugu language]] films.<ref name=c>{{cite news|url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-metroplus/this-film-came-at-the-right-time/article6902995.ece|title=This film came at the right time|newspaper=The Hindu|accessdate=30 August 2017|date=17 February 2015|last1=Chowdhary|first1=Y. Sunita}}</ref> He debuted in 2011 with [[Ravi Babu]]'s romantic comedy ''[[Nuvvila]]'' (2011), but he gained recognition with his supporting role in the coming-of-age drama ''[[Yevade Subramanyam]]'' (2015). Vijay gained stardom by playing the lead role in the 2016 [[romantic comedy]] ''[[Pelli Choopulu]]'', which won the [[National Film Award for Best Feature Film in Telugu]] and the [[Filmfare Award for Best Film - Telugu]]. \n\nSubsequently, Vijay has established himself as a leading actor of [[Telugu cinema]] by starring in lead roles in critical and commercial successes such as ''[[Arjun Reddy]]'' (2017), ''[[Mahanati]]'' (2018), ''[[Geetha Govindam]]'' (2018), and ''[[Taxiwaala]]'' (2018), some of which rank among the [[list of highest-grossing Telugu films]]. His performance in ''[[Arjun Reddy]]'' won him several accolades, including the [[Filmfare Award for Best Actor - Telugu]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/magazine/leisure/story/20171002-vijay-sai-deverakonda-telugu-cinema-arjun-reddy-sandeep-reddy-vanga-1049492-2017-09-23|title=Serial kisser Deverakonda is the Emraan Hashmi of Telugu cinema|first1=Mona |last1=Ramavat|date=23 September 2017|website=India Today|accessdate=11 February 2020}}</ref><ref name=a>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_pqngUO_pP4|title=Yevade Subramanyam Theatrical Trailer - Nani, Malavika Nair|last=Vyjayanthi Network|date=15 January 2015|publisher=|accessdate=30 August 2017|via=YouTube}}</ref> In 2019, he won the [[South Indian International Movie Awards|South Indian International Movie Critics Award for Best Actor]] and was also nominated for the [[Filmfare Award for Best Actor - Telugu]] for his work in  ''[[Geetha Govindam]]''.<ref>{{cite web|author=P Kirubhakar |url=https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/regional-cinema/story/siima-2019-vijay-deverakonda-and-keerthy-suresh-win-big-see-pics-1581463-2019-08-16 |title=SIIMA 2019: Vijay Deverakonda and Keerthy Suresh win big. See pics - Movies News |publisher=Indiatoday.in |date= |accessdate=17 August 2019}}</ref>\n\nHe owns a film production company, King of the Hill Entertainment and was featured by ''[[Forbes India|Forbes india]]'' in their [[Forbes 30 Under 30|30 Under 30]] list of 2019.<ref name=\"ProductionHouse\"/><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.forbesindia.com/thirtyprofile2019/vijay-deverakonda/1755/21|title=Vijay Deverakonda - Forbes India Magazine|website=Forbes India|language=en|access-date=11 November 2019}}</ref> According to the annual report by the search engine Google, He was the most searched South Indian actor in 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/vijay-deverakonda-is-the-most-searched-south-indian-actor-in-2019/articleshow/72490028.cms|title=Vijay Deverakonda is the most-searched South Indian actor in 2019 - Times of India|website=The Times of India|language=en|access-date=2020-03-05}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nDeverakonda says, his family used to call him a ''rowdy'' every time he did something not approved by them. Over time, he started to use the term for himself and his fans.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/telugu/2018/jul/17/homegrown-actor-vijay-deverakonda-redefines-rowdy-1844400.html|title=Homegrown actor Vijay Deverakonda redefines 'Rowdy'|publisher=The Indian Express|date=17 July 2018 |accessdate=4 August 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/with-nota-vijay-devarakonda-is-all-set-to-conquer-tamil-audiences-what-makes-the-young-star-so-popular-5322251.html/amp|title=Vijay Devarakonda likes to call it 'Rowdy'|publisher=First post|date=5 October 2018 |accessdate=4 August 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Career ==\n===Early career and struggle (2011\u20132015)===\nDeverakonda made his film debut by starring in Ravi Babu's romantic comedy [[Nuvvila]] in 2011,{{cn|date=March 2019}} and then had a small cameo role in [[Sekhar Kammula]]'s ''[[Life Is Beautiful (2012 film)|Life is Beautiful]]''. Both films were decently successful but failed to give Deverakonda much recognition.<ref name=h>{{cite web|url=http://movies.ndtv.com/regional/shekhar-kammulas-telugu-film-life-is-beautiful-pushed-to-september-14-607260|title=NDTV Movies: Regional-Movies - Tamil Movies - Telugu Movies - Bengali Movies - Latest Movie News - Celebrity Gossip|website=movies.ndtv.com|accessdate=30 August 2017}}</ref> Then, he was introduced to an assistant director at the time, [[Nag Ashwin]], who later cast him in a supporting role for the 2015 movie ''[[Yevade Subramanyam]]'' alongside actor [[Nani (actor)|Nani]].<ref name=i>{{cite news|url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/metroplus/an-eye-for-story/article6874716.ece|title=An eye for story|newspaper=The Hindu|accessdate=30 August 2017|date=9 February 2015|last1=Chowdhary|first1=Y. Sunita}}</ref> The film was produced by the daughters of [[Ashwini Dutt]], a producer in the Telugu film industry. [[Priyanka Dutt]] backed him, and once shooting started, Swapna Dutt signed him onto her company.<ref name=j>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=oSstKbH8NQg|title=Swapna Dutt Speech - Yevade Subramanyam Audio Launch Live - Nani, Malavika Nair|last=Vyjayanthi Network|date=21 February 2015|publisher=|accessdate=30 August 2017|via=YouTube}}</ref><ref name=k>{{cite web|url=http://www.radiokhushi.com/news/details/1501/Evade-Subramanyam-says-Nani|title='Evade Subramanyam' says Nani|last=Radiokhushi|website=www.radiokhushi.com|accessdate=30 August 2017}}</ref> The film went on to be a critical and commercial success, and Deverakonda won high praise for his diction, energy, and role in the movie. This movie finally gave him a much-desired break in [[Telugu language|Telugu]] cinema.{{cn|date=March 2019}}\n\n===Breakthrough and success (2015\u2013present)===\nVijay's first lead role was in ''[[Pelli Choopulu]]'', a romantic coming-of-age entertainer directed by [[Tharun Bhascker Dhaassyam]], with [[Ritu Varma]] as the female lead. The film went on to be commercially successful<ref name=m>{{cite web|url=http://epaperbeta.timesofindia.com/Article.aspx?eid=31809&articlexml=VIJAY-DEVERAKONDA-SIGNS-HIS-NEXT-08062015108013|title=The Times Group|website=epaperbeta.timesofindia.com|accessdate=30 August 2017}}</ref> and won the [[National Film Award for Best Feature Film in Telugu|Best Feature Film in Telugu]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.timesofindia.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/pelli-choopulu-bags-two-national-awards-is-best-film-in-telugu/amp_articleshow/58066962.cms|title=Pelli Choopulu bags two national awards; is 'best film' in Telugu|publisher=Times of India|date=8 April 2017}}</ref> at the [[64th National Film Awards]] as well as the [[Filmfare Award for Best Film - Telugu]]. He received praise for his realistic portrayal of a lazy and unmotivated chef.{{Citation needed|date=September 2018}} He then starred in a masala entertainer, ''[[Dwaraka (film)|Dwaraka]]'' in 2017. His next film ''[[Arjun Reddy]]'' received praise and criticism alike for being very bold and radical. Vijay's portrayal as a self-destructive, short-tempered, and alcoholic surgeon received critical acclaim, which led to him winning numerous awards, including the [[Filmfare Award for Best Actor - Telugu]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.thenewsminute.com/article/womens-groups-protest-against-arjun-reddy-vijayawada-demand-ban-films-screening-67695|title=Women's groups protest against 'Arjun Reddy' in Vijayawada, demand ban on film's screening|date=1 September 2017|work=The News Minute|access-date=3 September 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/movie-reviews/arjun-reddy-movie-review-intense-raw-and-unbelievably-honest-5-stars/story-kSroTBJoqiGlTBavkdlVeK.html|title=Arjun Reddy movie review: Intense, raw and unbelievably honest. 5 stars|date=26 August 2017|work=Hindustan Times|access-date=27 August 2017}}</ref> Following ''[[Arjun Reddy]]'' was ''[[Ye Mantram Vesave]]'', which was delayed for 5 years and finally released. It was given poor reviews from critics and could not fare well at the box office. He then starred in ''[[Mahanati]]'', a biographical period film around life of actress [[Savitri (actress)|Savitri]]. He won acclaim for playing a charismatic and easy going photographer. Deverakonda's next release in 2018 was [[Geetha Arts]]' romantic comedy ''[[Geetha Govindam]]'', in which he starred as an innocent and nervous college professor. Deverakonda received praise for playing a subtle, boy-next-door character after an aggressive role in Arjun Reddy. His next film, released on 5 October, was the Tamil political thriller ''[[NOTA (film)|NOTA]]'', directed by ''[[Iru Mugan]]''-fame [[Anand Shankar]]. It performed poorly at the box office.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.telugu360.com/nota-worldwide-closing-collections-disaster/|title='NOTA' Worldwide Closing Collections - Disaster|date=27 October 2018|work=Telugu360.com|access-date=28 October 2018|language=en-US}}</ref> His next project was [[UV Creations]]' supernatural comedy thriller ''[[Taxiwala]]'' in which Vijay stumbles upon a possessed car opposite [[Priyanka Jawalkar]].\nIn 2019, Deverakonda was seen in [[Bharat Kamma]]'s ''[[Dear Comrade]]'', a romantic action drama, once again alongside [[Rashmika Mandanna]]. His upcoming film is [[Kranthi Madhav]]'s romantic drama titled [[World Famous Lover]] opposite [[Rashi Khanna]], [[Catherine Tresa]], [[Aishwarya Rajesh]] and [[Izabelle Leite]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.deccanchronicle.com/entertainment/tollywood/211018/vijay-deverakondas-new-film-rolls-out.html |title=Vijay Deverakonda's new film rolls out! |publisher=Deccanchronicle.com |date= 21 October 2018|accessdate=17 August 2019}}</ref> He will next be seen in Hero, a Telugu film that will be dubbed in Tamil and Malayalam too. The movie will be directed by Anand Annamalai, co-writer of films like [[Kuttrame Thandanai|Kuttramae Thandanai]] and [[Kaaka Muttai|Kaakka Muttai]]. The film see [[Malavika Mohanan]] essay the role of Vijay's love interest. Vijay will be taking on the role of a biker in this film.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.in.com/entertainment/regional/vijay-devarakonda-malavika-mohanans-hero-gets-launched-biker-rajini-krishnan-to-train-the-hero-415343.htm|title=Vijay Devarakonda and Malavika Mohanan's Hero gets launched; biker Rajini Krishnan to train the Hero!|website=in.com|language=en|access-date=24 May 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://mumbaimirror.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/malavika-mohanan-and-vijay-devarakonda-in-anand-annamalais-hero/articleshow/69402713.cms|title=Malavika Mohanan and Vijay Devarakonda in Anand Annamalai's Hero|last=Coutinho|first=Natasha CoutinhoNatasha|last2=May 20|first2=Mumbai Mirror {{!}} Updated|website=Mumbai Mirror|language=en|access-date=24 May 2019|last3=2019|last4=Ist|first4=11:51}}</ref>\n\nDeverakonda was placed 72nd in the [[Forbes India]] Celebrity 100 list 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.forbesindia.com/lists/2018-celebrity-100/1735/1|title=2018 Celebrity 100|website=[[Forbes India]]|accessdate=5 December 2018}}</ref> In 2019, ''[[Film Companion]]'' ranked Deverakonda's performance in ''[[Arjun Reddy]]'' among ''100 Greatest Performances of the decade.''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.filmcompanion.in/best-of-the-decade/100-best-performances-indian-cinema.html|title=100 Greatest Performances of the Decade|website=100 Greatest Performances of the Decade|language=en|access-date=26 November 2019}}</ref>\n\nDeverakonda made his debut in [[Hindi]] films with [[Karan Johar]] produced ''Fighter''. Directed by [[Puri Jagannadh]], the film went on floors in January 2020.<ref>{{cite news |title=Vijay Deverakonda's Hindi debut reportedly titled Fighter; Karan Johar-produced film goes on floors- Entertainment News, Firstpost |url=https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/vijay-deverakondas-hindi-debut-reportedly-titled-fighter-karan-johar-produced-film-goes-on-floors-7930971.html |accessdate=6 March 2020 |work=Firstpost |date=20 January 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n\n===King of the Hill Entertainment===\nDeverakonda is the owner of a film production company, King of the Hill Entertainment.<ref name=\"ProductionHouse\">{{cite news |title=Vijay Deverakonda: I want to create a platform for new talent |url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/telugu/vijay-deverakonda-i-want-to-create-a-platform-for-new-talent-6103938/ |accessdate=13 January 2020 |work=The Indian Express |date=5 November 2019}}</ref> Its debut film, ''[[Meeku Maathrame Cheptha]]'' was released in November 2019.<ref>{{cite news |title=Vijay Deverkonda Turns Producer, Announces Debut Production Meeku Maathrame Cheptha |url=https://www.news18.com/news/movies/vijay-deverkonda-turns-producer-announces-film-with-meeku-maathrame-cheptha-2289531.html |accessdate=13 January 2020 |work=News18 |date=29 August 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Brands and endorsements==\nOn 11 February 2020, Deverakonda launched his fashion brand \u2018Rowdy Wear\u2019 on e-commerce portal [[Myntra]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Actor Vijay Deverakonda launches his fashion brand 'Rowdy Wear' on Myntra |url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/actor-vijay-deverakonda-launches-his-fashion-brand-rowdy-wear-myntra-117989 |accessdate=12 February 2020 |work=[[The News Minute]] |date=12 February 2020}}</ref> He was the brand ambassador of food delivery app [[Zomato]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Vijay Deverakonda as Zomato brand ambassador - TV9 |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SQzjp60hUeo |accessdate=6 March 2020 |work=[[TV9 Telugu]] |date=22 August 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+Key\n| style=\"background:#ffc;\"| {{dagger|alt=Films that have not yet been released}}\n| Denotes films that have not yet been released\n|}\n\n\u2022 All the films are in [[Telugu language]], unless otherwise noted.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|- \n! Year\n! Film\n! Role(s)\n! Notes\n! Ref\n|-\n| 2011\n| ''[[Nuvvila]]''\n| Vishnu\n| Film debut\n|\n|-\n| 2012\n| ''[[Life Is Beautiful (2012 film)|Life Is Beautiful]]''\n| Ajay\n| Villain \n|\n|-\n| 2015\n| ''[[Yevade Subramanyam]]''\n| Rishi\n| Supporting role\n|\n|-\n| 2016\n| ''[[Pelli Choopulu]]''\n| Prasanth\n| First lead role\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |2017\n| ''[[Dwaraka (film)|Dwaraka]]''\n| Erra Srinu / Sri Krishnananda Swamy\n|\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Arjun Reddy]]''\n| Dr. Arjun Reddy Deshmukh\n| [[Filmfare Award for Best Actor - Telugu]]\n|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movies-cinema-news-16/winners-list-of-behindwoods-gold-medal-awards-2018.html|title=Winners list of Behindwoods Gold Medal Awards 2018|date=17 June 2018|publisher=}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"6\" |2018\n| ''[[Ye Mantram Vesave]]''\n| Nikhil \"Nikki\"\n|\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Mahanati]]''\n|  Vijay Anthony\n|[[Bilingual]] in [[Tamil language|Tamil]] as <br />''Nadigaiyar Thilagam''\n|\n|-\n|''[[Geetha Govindam]]''\n| Vijay Govind\n|Nominated- [[Filmfare Award for Best Actor - Telugu]]\n|\n|-\n|''[[NOTA (film)|NOTA]]''\n| Varun Subramanyam\n| Tamil film, dubbed and released in Telugu\n|\n|-\n|''[[Ee Nagaraniki Emaindhi]]''\n| Vijay\n| Cameo appearance\n|\n|-\n|''[[Taxiwaala]]''\n| Shiva\n| \n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 2019\n|''[[Dear Comrade]]''\n| Comrade Chaitanya Krishnan (Bobby) \n| Dubbed into Kannada, Malayalam and Tamil \n| <ref name=\"NIE\">{{cite news |title=Dear Comrade will not see Hindi version |url=https://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/telugu/2019/jul/13/dear-comrade-will-not-see-hindi-version-2003232.html |accessdate=15 July 2019 |work=New Indian Express |date=13 July 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''[[Meeku Maathrame Cheptha]]''\n|Vijay Kumar\n|Cameo Appearance\n|\n|-\n|rowspan=\"5\"| 2020\n|''[[World Famous Lover]]''\n| Gautham / Union Leader Seenayya(Srinu)\n| \n|<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.telugu360.com/vijay-devarakondas-world-famous-lover/ |title=Vijay Devarakonda's World Famous Lover |accessdate=17 September 2019 |work=Telugu 360 Indian |date=17 September 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n|''Hero''\n|\n|Filming\n|<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/regional-cinema/story/vijay-deverakonda-and-malavika-mohanan-s-film-hero-shelved-this-is-why-1574137-2019-07-27|title=Vijay Deverakonda as main lead in Anand Annamalai's next|work=India Today |date=27 July 2019| accessdate= 11 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cinemaexpress.com/stories/news/2019/mar/13/title-clash-between-the-films-of-sivakarthikeyan-and-vijay-devarakonda-10520.html|title= Movie title clash between Vijay Deverakonda and Siva Karthikeyan|accessdate= 11 January 2020|work=Cinema Express|date=13 March 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n|''Fighter''\n|\n|Filming\n|<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/movies/vijay-deverakonda-starts-shooting-for-puri-jagannadhs-fighter/article30606252.ece |title=Puri Jagannadh's Fighter |accessdate=10 February 2020|newspaper=The Hindu |date=20 January 2020}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==As producer==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-  style=\"background:#ccc; text-align:center;\"\n! Year\n! Film\n! Director\n! Notes\n! Ref\n|-\n| 2019\n| ''[[Meeku Maathrame Cheptha]]''\n| Shammeer Sultan\n|  Producer\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/meeku-mathrame-cheptha-teaser-vijay-deverakondas-maiden-production-sees-tharun-bhascker-as-a-lying-bloke-7301311.html|title=Meeku Mathrame Cheptha teaser: Vijay Deverakonda's maiden production sees Tharun Bhascker as a lying bloke|date=7 September 2019|website=Firstpost|language=en|access-date=16 October 2019}}</ref>\n|}\n\n== Awards and nominations ==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Year\n!Award\n!Category\n!Film\n!Result\n|-\n| | 2015\n| [[Nandi Awards]] \n|Special Jury Award - [[Telugu language|Telugu]]\n| |''[[Yevade Subramanyam]]''\n|  {{Won}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\"| 2017\n| [[Filmfare Awards South]] \n|Best Actor - [[Telugu language|Telugu]]\n| rowspan=\"3\" |''[[Arjun Reddy]]''\n| rowspan=3 {{Won}}\n|-\n| [[Zee Telugu]] Golden Awards\n|Golden Awards for Best Actor\n|-\n| Behindwoods Gold Medal \n|The South Indian Sensation\n|-\n| | 2018\n| [[Zee Telugu]] Golden Awards\n| Favourite Actor\n| rowspan=\"2\"|''[[Geetha Govindam]]''\n| {{Won}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\" |2019\n| Sri Kala Sudha Telugu Association Awards\n| Best Actor\n| {{Won}}\n|-\n| Hindustan times India's most stylish 2019 Awards\n| Hottest stylista\n|\n| {{Won}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" |[[South Indian International Movie Awards|SIIMA Film Awards]]\n|Best Actor (Critics) - Telugu\n|''[[Geetha Govindam]]''\n| {{Won}}\n|-\n|Popular Celebrity on Social Media\n|\n| {{Won}}\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons Category|Vijay Devarakonda}}\n* {{IMDb name|4797922}}\n*{{Facebook|TheDeverakonda}}\n\n{{FilmfareTeluguBestActor}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Deverakonda, Vijay}}\n[[Category:1989 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Male actors from Hyderabad, India]]\n[[Category:Telugu people]]\n[[Category:Filmfare Awards South winners]]\n[[Category:Male actors in Telugu cinema]]\n[[Category:Indian male film actors]]\n[[Category:Indian male stage actors]]\n[[Category:21st-century Indian male actors]]\n", "name_user": "183.83.247.199", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vijay_Deverakonda"}
{"title_page": "Magda Goebbels", "text_new": "{{Infobox First Lady\n| name = Magda Goebbels\n| image = Bundesarchiv Bild 183-R22014, Magda Goebbels.jpg\n| caption = Goebbels in 1933\n|birth_name=Johanna Maria Magdalena Ritschel\n| birth_date = {{birth date|1901|11|11|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Berlin]], [[German Empire]]\n| death_date = {{death date and age|df=yes|1945|5|1|1901|11|11}}\n| death_place = [[F\u00fchrerbunker]], Berlin, [[Nazi Germany]]\n| restingplace = \n| alma_mater = [[Ursuline Convent]] \n| profession = [[Propagandist]]\n| office1=\n| term_start1= \n| term_end1= \n| successor1= \n| party = [[National Socialist German Workers' Party]] (NSDAP)\n| spouse = {{plainlist |\n* {{marriage|[[G\u00fcnther Quandt]]|1921|1929|reason=divorced}}\n* {{marriage|[[Joseph Goebbels]]|1931|1945|reason=died}}\n }}\n| children = 7\n| awards =[[Golden Party Badge]] [[File:\u041f\u043b\u0430\u043d\u043a\u0430 \u0417\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0442\u043e\u0439 \u043f\u0430\u0440\u0442\u0438\u0439\u043d\u044b\u0439 \u0437\u043d\u0430\u043a \u041d\u0421\u0414\u0410\u041f.svg|50px]]<br>[[Cross of Honor of the German Mother]]\n|parents=Auguste Behrend<br>Oskar Ritschel}}\n\n'''Johanna Maria Magdalena''' \"'''Magda'''\" '''Goebbels''' ([[Married and maiden names|n\u00e9e]] '''Ritschel'''; 11 November 1901 \u2013 1 May 1945) was the wife of [[Nazi Germany]]'s Propaganda Minister [[Joseph Goebbels]]. A prominent member of the [[Nazi Party]], she was a close ally, companion and political supporter of [[Adolf Hitler]].<ref name=\"hisext\">{{cite web |last1=Wyllie |first1=James |title=Nazi wives: the women beside Hess, Goebbels, G\u00f6ring and Himmler |url=https://www.historyextra.com/period/20th-century/nazi-wives-women-who-ilse-hess-magda-goebbels-emmy-goring/ |website=HistoryExtra |publisher=BBC History Revealed |accessdate=11 February 2020 |date=February 2020}}</ref> Some historians refer to her as the unofficial \"[[First Lady]]\" of Nazi Germany, while others give that title to [[Emmy G\u00f6ring]].{{sfn|Thacker|2010|p=179}}{{sfn|Longerich|2015|pp=159, 160}}\n\nWith defeat imminent during the [[Battle of Berlin]] at the end of [[World War II]] in Europe, she and her husband murdered their [[Goebbels children|six children]] before committing [[suicide]] in the [[Reich Chancellery]] gardens. Her eldest son, [[Harald Quandt]], from a previous marriage, survived her.\n\n==Early life==\nMagda was born in 1901 in [[Berlin]], [[German Empire|Germany]] to unwed Auguste Behrend and building contractor and engineer, Oskar Ritschel.{{sfn|Longerich|2015|p=151}} The couple were married later that year and divorced in either 1904 or 1905.<ref name=dhm> [http://www.dhm.de/lemo/html/biografien/GoebbelsMagda/index.html Magda Goebbels biography] at Deutsches Historisches Museum, Berlin</ref>{{sfn|Longerich|2015|p=151}} Yet some sources suggest that the marriage was before Magda's birth, but there is no evidence to support such a prior wedding.<ref name=arditti>Arditti, Michael, [http://www.michaelarditti.com/non-fiction/magda goebbels-by-anja-klabunde/ ''Magda Goebbels'' by Anja Klabunde] Literary Review, 22 May 2002</ref>{{sfn|Meissner|1980|p=13}} When Magda was five, her mother sent her to [[Cologne]] to stay with her ex-husband.  In 1908, her mother married [[Richard Friedl\u00e4nder]], a wealthy Jewish merchant who worked in Brussels, who adopted Magda and whose surname she adopted.{{sfn|Longerich|2015|pp=151, 152}}  In Brussels, Magda was enrolled at the Ursuline Convent in [[Vilvoorde]]{{sfn|Meissner|1980|p=16}} where she was remembered as \"an active and intelligent little girl\".<ref>de Launay, Jaques, ''Hitler en Flandres'', 1975</ref>  During numerous visits to her father Ritschel, who lived in Duisburg and was a member of a Krefeld Masonic Lodge, Magda may have been introduced to Buddhism.<ref>{{cite web|title=Historie|periodical=|publisher=|url=http://www.freimaurer-krefeld.de/index.php/historie|url-status=|format=|access-date=|archive-url=|archive-date=|last=|date=|year=|language=|pages=|quote=}}</ref>\n\nIn 2016, it was reported that Friedl\u00e4nder may have been actually Magda's biological father, as stated in his residency card, discovered in Berlin archives by writer and historian [[Oliver Hilmes]].<ref name=\"thejc.com\"> [http://www.thejc.com/news/world-news/162206/magda-goebbels-biological-father-may-have-been-jewish Magda Goebbels' biological father may have been Jewish] Jewish Chronicle. 21 August 2016. Retrieved 22 August 2016.</ref>{{sfn|Meissner|1980|p=16}}{{sfn|Longerich|2015|pp=151, 152}} Hence, Magda's adoption upon her parents' delayed wedding may have been required merely to update the girls 'illegitimate child' status.<ref>Magda Goebbels, Gef\u00e4hrtin des B\u00f6sen In:  Der Spiegel Vol. 39, 24. September 2001 [http://www.spiegel.de/spiegel/print/d-20184307.html]</ref> \n\nFrom 1908 until the outbreak of [[World War I]], the family remained in Brussels. At that time, all Germans were forced to leave Belgium as refugees to avoid repercussions from the Belgian people after the German invasion.<ref name=\"dhm\" /> The family moved to Berlin where Magda attended the high school Kolmorgen Lyc\u00e9e. Behrend divorced Friedl\u00e4nder in 1914, and in 1919, Magda was enrolled in the prestigious Holzhausen Ladies' College near [[Goslar]].<ref name=\"dhm\" /> While in Berlin, Magda also befriended Lisa Arlosoroff and became intimate with her brother Haim, an ardent Zionist.{{sfn|Shindler|2017|pp=46\u201347}} During her relationship with Arlosoroff, she briefly wore a Star of David he had given her and even attended meetings of Tikvat Zion; the relationship did not last but the two remained in contact during the 1920s.{{sfn|Shindler|2017|p=47}}\n\n==Marriage and son with G\u00fcnther Quandt==\nIn 1920, while returning to school on a train, she met [[G\u00fcnther Quandt]], a rich German industrialist twice her age.{{sfn|Longerich|2015|p=152}} Thereafter, he courted her with courtesy and grand gestures.{{sfn|Meissner|1980|p=29}} He demanded that she change her surname back to Ritschel (having borne many years the surname of Friedl\u00e4nder), when converting from [[Catholicism]] to Quand's [[Protestantism|Protestant church]].{{sfn|Meissner|1980|p=31}} They were married on 4 January 1921, and her first child, [[Harald Quandt|their Harald]], was born on 1 November 1921.{{sfn|Thacker|2010|p=149}}\n\nMagda soon grew frustrated in her marriage because Quandt spent little time with her. His main interest seemed to be the expansion of his business empire.{{sfn|Longerich|2015|p=152}} She was left to look after six children - Harald, with Quandt's two sons from prior marriage, and three children from a deceased friend, then run the whole household.{{sfn|Longerich|2015|p=152}}\n\nIn October 1927, the couple went on a two month visit to the United States, to conduct a business with the Lloyd Electric Storage Battery Co. of  [[Philadelphia]].<ref>''List or Manifest of Alien Passengers For the United States Immigration Officer At the Port of Arrival'' (Form 500 U.S. Department of Labor, Immigration Service), pp. 7\u20138, number on list 3 & 4, dated October 22 & 28, 1927.</ref>  In 1929, Quandt discovered that Magda was having an affair, so they separated, then went on to divorce that same year, which terms were however quite generous with Magda.{{sfn|Longerich|2015|p=152}}\n\n==Marriage and family with Joseph Goebbels==\n[[File:Bundesarchiv Bild 183-R32860, Berlin, Trauung von Joseph und Magda Goebbels.jpg|left|thumb|Joseph and Magda's wedding day, with her son Harald Quandt in his [[Deutsches Jungvolk]] uniform. [[Adolf Hitler]], their [[best man]], can be seen in the background.]]\n\nIn 1930, Magda attended a meeting of the [[Nazi Party]] where she was impressed by one of the speakers, [[Joseph Goebbels]], then the [[Gauleiter]] of Berlin. On 1 September 1930, she joined the party to do some volunteer work, although not characterized before as politically active, and '''more amazing''', regardless her  partly Jewish parental decent, and her obvious positive attitude towards others' religion and culture.  From the local branch, Magda moved to the party headquarters in Berlin and for a brief period became secretary to Hans Meinshausen, Goebbels' deputy, before being invited to take charge of Goebbels' own private papers.{{sfn|Meissner|1980|p=82}} She and Goebbels became romantically involved while on a short trip with friends to Weimar in February 1931.{{sfn|Longerich|2015|p=152}} A relationship began and by April they began making plans for their future together.{{sfn|Longerich|2015|p=153}} Goebbels wrote in his diary, \"We have made a solemn vow to each other: When we have conquered the [[Reich]], we will become man and wife. I am very happy.\"{{sfn|Longerich|2015|p=153}} Her flat on [[Theodor-Heuss-Platz]] (then named the ''Reichskanzlerplatz'') soon became a favourite meeting place for [[Adolf Hitler]] and other NSDAP officials.{{sfn|Manvell|Fraenkel|2010|p=94}}\n\nBy September, the relationship was experiencing problems. Goebbels was often jealous, and had some concern over the fact that Hitler had grown fond of Magda.{{sfn|Longerich|2015|pp=153, 157, 158}} Magda decided to move forward their wedding date,{{sfn|Longerich|2015|p=153}} and the couple were married on 19 December 1931, with Hitler as a witness.{{sfn|Longerich|2015|p=167}}  [[Otto Wagener]] claims that Magda's marriage to Goebbels was somewhat arranged; since Hitler intended to remain unmarried, it was suggested that as the wife of a leading and highly visible Nazi official she might eventually act as \"first lady of the [[Third Reich]]\".  Magda was a very ambitious woman with social connections and upper class bearing that may have influenced Goebbels' own enthusiasm.<ref name=wagener>Wagener, Otto, ''Hitler: Memoirs of a Confidant''</ref> Goebbels biographer [[Peter Longerich]] concurred with this \"plausible\" conclusion as.{{sfn|Longerich|2015|pp=159, 160}} Meissner contends that Hitler (though undoubtedly impressed by Magda) was an exceptionally close friend of the couple in the early days. Hitler enjoyed staying at the Goebbels' Berlin apartment, where he could relax,{{sfn|Longerich|2015|p=160}} and he grew very fond of the Goebbels' children.{{sfn|Longerich|2015|pp=159, 160}} Hitler would often arrive there late at night, sitting and talking with Goebbels, with the baby Helga (born 1932) on his lap.{{sfn|Meissner|1980|pp=91, 97\u201399}} [[File:Bundesarchiv Bild 146-1978-086-03, Joseph Goebbels mit Familie.jpg|thumb|The Goebbels family in 1942: (back row) Hildegard, [[Harald Quandt]], Helga; (front row) Helmut, Hedwig, Magda, Heidrun, [[Joseph Goebbels|Joseph]] and Holdine. (In this well-known [[manipulated image]],{{refneeded|date=April 2020}} the visage of the uniformed Harald, who was actually away on military duties, was inserted and retouched.)]]\n\nMagda had a close relationship with Hitler, and became a member of his small coterie of female friends.{{sfn|Manvell|Fraenkel|2010|p=94}} She acted as an unofficial representative of the regime, receiving letters from all over Germany from women with questions about domestic matters or child custody issues.{{sfn|Thacker|2010|p=179}} After 1933, the Goebbels family became accustomed to the luxurious lifestyle which went with their high social position. Their Berlin home on G\u00f6ringstrasse was remodeled by [[Albert Speer]] and they spent the spring and summers in Kladow.{{sfn|Longerich|2015|pp=231, 290\u2013291}} In 1936, they bought a villa on Schwanenwerder island and later another at Bogensee near Wandlitz in Brandenburg.{{sfn|Longerich|2015|pp=315, 316}}\n\n{{main|Goebbels children}}\nJoseph and Magda Goebbels had six children: Helga Susanne (1932), Hildegard \"Hilde\" Traudel (1934), Helmut Christian (1935), Holdine \"Holde\" Kathrin (1937), Hedwig \"Hedda\" Johanna (1938), and Heidrun \"Heide\" Elisabeth (1940).{{sfn|Manvell|Fraenkel|2010|p=165}} [[File:Bogensee 25.jpg|thumb|Goebbels' villa on Bogensee,<br>2008 condition]] Yet, Joseph Goebbels had many affairs during the marriage. In 1936, Goebbels met the [[Czech people|Czech]] actress [[L\u00edda Baarov\u00e1]] and by the winter of 1937 began an intense affair with her.{{sfn|Longerich|2015|pp=317, 318}} Magda had a long conversation with Hitler about the situation on 15 August 1938.{{sfn|Longerich|2015|p=392}} Unwilling to put up with a scandal involving one of his top ministers, Hitler demanded that Goebbels break off the relationship.{{sfn|Manvell|Fraenkel|2010|p=170}} Thereafter, Goebbels and Magda seemed to reach a truce until the end of September.{{sfn|Longerich|2015|p=392}} The couple had another falling out at that point, and once again Hitler became involved, insisting the couple stay together.{{sfn|Longerich|2015|pp=392\u2013395}} Hitler arranged for publicity photos to be taken of himself with the reconciled couple in October 1938.{{sfn|Longerich|2015|pp=391, 395}}{{efn|In 1939 at the premiere of the film ''[[The Journey to Tilsit]]'', Magda ostentatiously left because the plot had an accidental resemblance to her situation and the affair between her husband and Baarov\u00e1. {{harv|Romani|1994|p=86}}}} Magda also had affairs, including a relationship with [[Kurt Ludecke]] in 1933{{sfn|Longerich|2015|p=317}} and [[Karl Hanke]] in 1938.{{sfn|Thacker|2010|p=204}}\n\n==War years==\nAt the outbreak of war, Magda's son by her first marriage, Harald Quandt, became a [[Luftwaffe]] pilot and fought at the front, while, at home, she lived up to the image of a patriotic mother by training as a [[German Red Cross|Red Cross]] nurse and working with the electronics company [[Telefunken]], and travelled to work on a bus, like her colleagues.<ref name=\"arditti\" /> She was also involved with entertaining the wives of the foreign heads of state, supporting the troops and comforting war widows.\n\nBoth Goebbels and Magda derived personal benefits and social status from their close association with Hitler, and the couple remained loyal to Hitler and publicly supported him. Privately, however, Magda expressed doubts, especially after the war began to go badly on the [[Eastern Front (World War II)|Eastern Front]]. On 9 November 1942, during a gathering with friends listening to a speech by Hitler, she switched off the radio exclaiming, \"My God, what a lot of rubbish.\"{{sfn|Meissner|1980|p=219}} In 1944, she reportedly said of Hitler, \"He no longer listens to voices of reason. Those who tell him what he wants to hear are the only ones he believes.\"{{sfn|Meissner|1980|p=222}}  There is no evidence that Magda attempted to intervene to save her Jewish stepfather from the [[Holocaust]]. Though his fate has not been established, it is widely assumed that he perished in the camps. Asked about her husband's [[antisemitism]], she answered: \"The F\u00fchrer wants it thus, and Joseph must obey.\"{{sfn|Meissner|1980|p=127}}\n\nFelix Franks, a German Jew who later became a British soldier, claimed that his grandparents got an [[exit visa]] from Germany with the help of Magda Goebbels:{{quote|My father and step-mother were left behind in Germany but, two days before the War started, they were asked to come to Gestapo Headquarters and given an exit visa. There is a story in the family which goes back to the First World War when my step-grandparents were asked to give shelter to a young woman who\u2019d been displaced by the war in Belgium. Although she had a Jewish step-father, she eventually married Joseph Goebbels! My stepmother believes she may have acted as a sort of protecting hand and was involved with the exit visa. Certainly, the night before Kristallnacht, they got an anonymous phone call warning my father not to go home that evening but to go somewhere safe. My step-mother swore it was Magda Goebbels.\"<ref name=arditti/><ref>Jewish Museum Berlin, major exhibition \"Home and Exile, The Jewish Quarterly.</ref>}}\n\nAfflicted with a weak heart and \"delicate health\", Magda would have extended periods of illness.{{sfn|Longerich|2015|pp=197, 361, 362, 706}} Towards the end of the war, she is known to have also suffered from severe depression and [[trigeminal neuralgia]].<ref>Klabunde, Anja, ''Magda Goebbels'', p. 302</ref> This condition affects a nerve in the face, and although usually harmless is considered to cause intense pain and can be notoriously hard to treat.<ref>[http://www.tna-support.org/ What is Trigeminal Neuralgia?] TNA Website</ref> This often left her bedridden and led to bouts of hospitalization as late as August 1944.{{sfn|Meissner|1980|pp=141, 228, 234}}\n\n==Death==\nIn late April 1945, the Soviet [[Red Army]] entered Berlin, and the Goebbels family moved into the ''[[Vorbunker]]'', connected to the lower ''[[F\u00fchrerbunker]]'' under the [[Reich Chancellery]] garden.{{sfn|Thacker|2010|p=298}} Magda wrote a farewell letter to her son Harald, who was in a [[prisoner of war|POW]] camp in [[North Africa]]:<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://spartacus-educational.com/Magda_Goebbels.htm|title=Magda Goebbels|work=Spartacus Educational|access-date=2017-04-26|language=en}}</ref>{{quote|My beloved son! By now we have been in the F\u00fchrerbunker for six days already\u2014daddy, your six little siblings and I, for the sake of giving our national socialistic lives the only possible honourable end ... You shall know that I stayed here against daddy's will, and that even on last Sunday the F\u00fchrer wanted to help me to get out. You know your mother\u2014we have the same blood, for me there was no wavering. Our glorious idea is ruined and with it everything beautiful and marvelous that I have known in my life. The world that comes after the F\u00fchrer and national socialism is not any longer worth living in and therefore I took the children with me, for they are too good for the life that would follow, and a merciful God will understand me when I will give them the salvation ... The children are wonderful ... there never is a word of complaint nor crying. The impacts are shaking the bunker. The elder kids cover the younger ones, their presence is a blessing and they are making the F\u00fchrer smile once in a while. May God help that I have the strength to perform the last and hardest. We only have one goal left: loyalty to the F\u00fchrer even in death. Harald, my dear son\u2014I want to give you what I learned in life: be loyal! Loyal to yourself, loyal to the people and loyal to your country ... Be proud of us and try to keep us in dear memory ...}}\n\nGoebbels added a postscript to Hitler's [[Last will and testament of Adolf Hitler|last will and testament]] of 29 April stating that he would disobey the order to leave Berlin, \"[f]or reasons of humanity and personal loyalty\". Further, he stated that Magda and their children supported his refusal to leave Berlin and his resolution to die in the bunker. He later qualified this by stating that the children would support the decision [to commit suicide] if they were old enough to speak for themselves.{{sfn|Longerich|2015|p=686}}\n\nMagda was among the last to see both Hitler and [[Eva Braun]] before they [[Death of Adolf Hitler|committed suicide]] on the afternoon of 30 April.{{sfn|Kershaw|2001|pp=827\u2013828}} On the following day, 1&nbsp;May, Magda and Joseph arranged for SS dentist [[Helmut Kunz]] to inject [[Goebbels children|their six children]] with [[morphine]] so that when they were unconscious, an ampule of [[cyanide]] could be then crushed in each of their mouths. Kunz later stated he gave the children morphine injections, but it was Magda and SS-''[[Obersturmbannf\u00fchrer]]'' [[Ludwig Stumpfegger]] (Hitler's personal doctor) who administered the cyanide.{{sfn|Beevor|2002|pp=380, 381}} Author [[James P. O'Donnell]] concluded that although Stumpfegger was probably involved in drugging the children, Magda killed them herself. He surmises that witnesses blamed the deaths on Stumpfegger because he was a convenient target, having died the following day. Moreover, as O'Donnell states, Stumpfegger may have been too intoxicated at the time of the deaths to have played a reliable role.{{sfn|O'Donnell|2001}}\n\nMagda appears to have contemplated and talked about killing her children a month in advance.{{sfn|Meissner|1980|p=242}} According to her friend and sister-in-law (from her first marriage) Ello Quandt, she told her that they were all going to take poison.\n{{quote|We have demanded monstrous things from the German people, treated other nations with pitiless cruelty. For this the victors will exact their full revenge...we can't let them think we are cowards. Everybody else has the right to live. We haven't got this right\u2014we have forfeited it. I make myself responsible. I belonged. I believed in Hitler and for long enough in Joseph Goebbels...Suppose I remain alive, I should immediately be arrested and interrogated about Joseph. If I tell the truth I must reveal what sort of man he was\u2014must describe all that happened behind the scenes. Then any respectable person would turn from me in disgust. It would be equally impossible to do the opposite\u2014that is to defend what he has done, to justify him to his enemies, to speak up for him out of true conviction...That would go against my conscience. So you see, Ello, it would be quite impossible for me to go on living. We will take the children with us, they are too good, too lovely for the world which lies ahead. In the days to come Joseph will be regarded as one of the greatest criminals that Germany has ever produced. His children would hear that said daily, people would torment them, despise and humiliate them. They would have to bear the burden of his sins and vengeance would be wreaked on them... It has all happened before. You know how I told you at the time quite frankly what the F\u00fchrer said in the Caf\u00e9 Anast in Munich when he saw the little Jewish boy, you remember? That he would like to squash him flat like a bug on the wall...I couldn't believe it and thought it was just provocative talk. But he really did it later. It was all so unspeakably gruesome...<ref>Klabunde, Anja, ''Magda Goebbels''</ref><ref>\"Ello Quandt testimony\"</ref>}}\n\nShe appears to have refused several offers, such as one by [[Albert Speer]], to have the children smuggled out of Berlin and insisted that the family must stay at her husband's side. In the ''F\u00fchrerbunker'' she confided to Hitler's secretary [[Traudl Junge]], that \"I would rather have my children die, than live in disgrace, jeered at. My children stand no chance in Germany after the war\".<ref>Junge, Traudl, ''Until the Final Hour''</ref>\n\nThe last survivor of Hitler's bunker, [[Rochus Misch]], gave this account of the events to the [[BBC]]:\n\n{{quote|Straight after Hitler's death, Mrs. Goebbels came down to the bunker with her children. She started preparing to kill them. She couldn't have done that above ground\u2014there were other people there who would have stopped her. That's why she came downstairs\u2014because no-one else was allowed in the bunker. She came down on purpose to kill them.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/europe/8234018.stm | work=BBC News | title=I was in Hitler's suicide bunker | date=3 September 2009 | accessdate=12 May 2010}}</ref>}}\n\nShe helped the girls change into long white nightgowns. She then softly combed their hair. Misch tried to concentrate on his work but he knew what was going to happen.{{sfn|Misch|2014|p=176}} Magda then went back up to the ''Vorbunker'' with the children. Shortly thereafter, [[Werner Naumann]] came down to the ''F\u00fchrerbunker'' and told Misch that he had seen Hitler's personal physician, Dr Stumpfegger give the children something \"sweetened\" to drink.{{sfn|Misch|2014|p=177}} About two hours later, Magda came back down to the ''F\u00fchrerbunker'', alone. She looked very pale, her eyes very red and her face was \"frozen\". She sat down at a table and began playing [[Patience (game)|patience]].{{sfn|Misch|2014|p=177}} Goebbels then came over to her, but did not say a word at that time.{{sfn|Misch|2014|p=177}}\n\nAfter their children were dead, Magda and Joseph Goebbels walked up to the garden of the Chancellery, where they committed [[suicide]].{{sfn|Joachimsthaler|1999|p=52}} There are several different accounts of this event. One account was that they each bit on a cyanide ampule near where Hitler had been buried, and were given a [[coup de gr\u00e2ce]] immediately afterwards.{{sfn|Beevor|2002|p=381}} Goebbels' SS adjutant [[G\u00fcnther Schw\u00e4germann]] testified in 1948 that they walked ahead of him up the stairs and out into the Chancellery garden. He waited in the stairwell and heard the shots sound. Schw\u00e4germann then walked up the remaining stairs and, once outside, saw their lifeless bodies. Following Goebbels' prior order, Schw\u00e4germann had an SS soldier fire several shots into Goebbels' body, which did not move.{{sfn|Joachimsthaler|1999|p=52}}{{efn|[[Johannes Hentschel]] later told Misch a singular conflicting story that Goebbels killed himself in his room in the bunker, and Magda in the ''Vorbunker'', during the early hours of 2&nbsp;May. {{harv|Misch|2014|pp=182, 183}}}} The bodies were then doused with [[gasoline|petrol]], but the remains were only partially burned and not buried.{{sfn|Beevor|2002|p=381}}\n\nThe charred corpses were found on the afternoon of 2 May 1945 by Soviet troops. Magda's face was unrecognizable compared to that of her husband.{{sfn|Ryan|1994|p=366}} The children were found in the ''Vorbunker'' dressed in their nightclothes, with ribbons tied in the girls' hair.{{sfn|Beevor|2002|p=398}} The remains of the Goebbels' family, Hitler, Eva Braun, General [[Hans Krebs (Wehrmacht general)|Hans Krebs]], and [[Blondi|Hitler's dogs]] were repeatedly buried and exhumed.{{sfn|Vinogradov|2005|pp=111, 333}} The last burial was at the [[SMERSH]] facility in [[Magdeburg]] on 21 February 1946. In 1970, [[KGB]] director [[Yuri Andropov]] authorised an operation to destroy the remains.{{sfn|Vinogradov|2005|p=333}} On 4 April 1970, a Soviet KGB team used detailed burial charts to exhume five wooden boxes at the Magdeburg facility. The remains from the boxes were burned, crushed, and scattered into the Biederitz river, a tributary of the nearby [[Elbe]].{{sfn|Vinogradov|2005|pp=335, 336}}\n\n== Portrayal in media ==\nMagda Goebbels has been portrayed by the following actresses in film and television productions.<ref name=\"imdb\">{{cite web | url = https://www.imdb.com/character/ch0042561/ | title = Magda Goebbels (Character) | accessdate = 8 May 2008 | author = | last = | first = | authorlink = | coauthors = | date = | year = | month = | format = | work = | publisher = [[IMDb.com]] | pages = | doi = | archiveurl = | archivedate = | quote = }}</ref>\n* Helga Kennedy-Dohrn in the 1955 West German film ''Der Letzte Akt'' (''Hitler: The Last Ten Days'').<ref name=\":1\" />\n* Yulia Dioshi in the 1971 Eastern Bloc co-production ''[[Liberation (film series)|Liberation: The Last Assault]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ssees.ucl.ac.uk/videos/dvds4801-4900.pdf|title=Library DVDs|date=12 September 2016|website=UCL SCHOOL OF SLAVONIC AND EAST EUROPEAN STUDIES (SSEES)|accessdate=27 April 2017}}</ref>\n* El\u00e9onore Hirt in the 1972 French television production ''Le Bunker''.\n* [[Marion Mathie]] in the 1973 British television production ''The Death of Adolf Hitler''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://frankfinlay.net/Television/Hitler.html|title=Frank Finlay|last=Josephdreams|website=frankfinlay.net|access-date=26 April 2017}}</ref>\n* [[Barbara Jefford]] in the 1973 British film ''[[Hitler: The Last Ten Days]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.unitedagents.co.uk/barbara-jefford|title=Barbara Jefford {{!}} United Agents|website=United Agents|language=en|access-date=26 April 2017}}</ref>\n* [[Piper Laurie]] in the 1981 United States television production ''[[The Bunker (1981 film)|The Bunker]]''.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1981/01/27/arts/tv-bunker-on-hitler-s-last-days.html|title=TV: 'BUNKER,' ON HITLER'S LAST DAYS|last=O'connor|first=John J.|date=27 January 1981|work=The New York Times|access-date=26 April 2017|issn=0362-4331}}</ref>\n* [[Elke Sommer]] in the 1982 United States television production ''[[Inside the Third Reich (film)|Inside the Third Reich]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.elkesommeronline.com/en/inside_the_third_reich.htm|title=Inside the Third Reich|website=Elke Sommer: The Official Website|access-date=26 April 2017}}</ref>\n* [[Hanna Schygulla]] in the 1998 Spanish comedy drama ''[[La ni\u00f1a de tus ojos]]'' (''The Girl of Your Dreams'').<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite book|title=Historical Dictionary of Holocaust Cinema|last=Reimer|first=Robert|publisher=Scarecrow Press|year=2012|isbn=|location=|pages=75}}</ref>\n* Yelena Spiridonova in the 1999 Russian drama ''[[Moloch]]''.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite book|title=The Hitler Filmography: Worldwide Feature Film and Television Miniseries Portrayals, 1940 through 2000|last=Mitchell|first=Charles P.|publisher=McFarland|year=2002|isbn=|location=|pages=}}</ref>\n* [[Eva Mattes]] in the 2001 German comedy ''Goebbels und Geduldig''.<ref name=\":0\" />\n* Jill Richardson in a 2003 episode of the British television series ''[[Days That Shook the World]]''.\n* [[Corinna Harfouch]] in the 2004 German film ''[[Downfall (2004 film)|''Downfall'' (''Der Untergang'')]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.newyorker.com/magazine/2005/02/14/back-in-the-bunker|title=Back in the Bunker|date=14 February 2005|website=The New Yorker|access-date=26 April 2017}}</ref>\n* Annette Uhlen in the 2004 German television production ''Propaganda''.{{citation needed|date=April 2017}}\n*Emma Buckley in the 2005 British television production ''Uncle Adolf''.{{citation needed|date=April 2017}}\n*[[Lenka Vlas\u00e1kov\u00e1]] in the 2016 Czech film ''The Devil's Mistress''\n*[[Katharina Heyer]] in the 2019 Netflix series ''Charit\u00e9 at War''\n\n==Notes==\n{{notelist}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n===Bibliography===\n{{refbegin}}\n* {{cite book | title = [[Berlin: The Downfall 1945]] | last = Beevor | first = Antony | authorlink = Antony Beevor | year = 2002 | publisher = Viking-Penguin Books | location = London | isbn = 978-0-670-03041-5 | ref = harv }}\n* [[Der Spiegel]] No. 35/04 ''Hitlers Ende Spiegels'' (H. 35, 2004)\n* E. Ebermayer, Hans Roos: ''Gef\u00e4hrtin des Teufels \u2013 Leben und Tod der Magda Goebbels'' (Hamburg, 1952)\n* Goebbels, Joseph: ''Tageb\u00fccher 1945 \u2013 Die letzten Aufzeichnungen'' (Hamburg, 1977) {{ISBN|3-404-01368-9}}\n* [http://www.dieterwunderlich.de/Klabunde_Goebbels.htm Anja Klabunde: Magda Goebbels \u2013 Ann\u00e4herung an ein Leben] (Munich, 1999) {{ISBN|3-570-00114-8}}\n* {{cite book | last = Joachimsthaler | first = Anton|authorlink=Anton Joachimsthaler | others = Trans. Helmut B\u00f6gler | title = The Last Days of Hitler: The Legends, the Evidence, the Truth | year = 1999 | origyear = 1995 | publisher = Brockhampton Press | location = London | isbn = 978-1-86019-902-8 | ref = harv}}\n* {{cite book | last = Kershaw | first = Ian | authorlink = Ian Kershaw | year = 2001 | origyear = 2000 | title = Hitler, 1936\u20131945: Nemesis | volume = 2 | publisher = W. W. Norton & Company | location = New York | isbn = 978-0-39-332252-1 | ref = harv}}\n* {{cite book | last = Longerich | first = Peter | year = 2015 | title = Goebbels: A Biography | publisher = Random House | location = New York | isbn = 978-1400067510 | ref = harv }}\n* {{cite book | last1 = Manvell | first1 = Roger | authorlink1 = Roger Manvell | last2 = Fraenkel | first2 = Heinrich | authorlink2 = Heinrich Fraenkel | title = Doctor Goebbels: His Life and Death | year = 2010| origyear = 1960 | publisher = Skyhorse | location = New York | isbn = 978-1-61608-029-7 | ref = harv}}\n* Meissner, Hans-Otto (1978). ''Magda Goebbels \u2013 Ein Lebensbild'' (Munich)\n* {{cite book | last = Meissner | first = Hans-Otto | title = Magda Goebbels: The First Lady of the Third Reich | year = 1980 | origyear = 1978 | publisher = The Dial Press | location = New York | isbn = 978-0803762121 | ref = harv }}\n* {{cite book | last = Misch | first = Rochus | title = Hitler's Last Witness: The Memoirs of Hitler's Bodyguard | publisher = Frontline Books-Skyhorse Publishing, Inc| location = London | year = 2014 | origyear = 2008 | isbn = 978-1848327498 | ref = harv }}\n* {{cite book | last = O'Donnell | first = James P. | authorlink = James P. O'Donnell | title = [[The Bunker (book)|The Bunker]] | year = 2001 | origyear = 1978 | publisher = Da Capo Press | location = New York | isbn = 978-0-306-80958-3 | ref = harv }}\n* {{cite book| last = Romani | first = Cinzia | title = Tainted Goddesses: Female Film Stars of the Third Reich | year = 1994 | publisher = Spellmount Publishers Ltd | page = 86 | ISBN = 978-1-87337-637-9 | ref = harv }}\n* {{cite book | last = Ryan | first = Cornelius | authorlink = Cornelius Ryan | year = 1994 | origyear = 1966 | title = The Last Battle | publisher = Simon & Schuster | location = New York | isbn = 978-1-439-12701-8 | ref = harv}}\n* Schaake, Erich (2000). ''Hitlers Frauen'' (Munich)\n* Schneider, Wolfgang (2001). ''Frauen unterm Hakenkreuz'' (Hamburg)\n* {{cite book | last=Shindler | first=Colin | year=2017 | title=The Hebrew Republic: Israel's Return to History | location=Lanham, MD | publisher= Rowman & Littlefield, | isbn=978-1-44226-596-7 | ref=harv}}\n* Sigmund, Anna Maria (1998). ''Die Frauen der Nazis'' Volume 1, (Vienna) {{ISBN|3-8000-3699-1}}\n* {{cite book | last = Thacker | first = Toby | title = Joseph Goebbels: Life and Death | year = 2010 | origyear = 2009 | publisher = Palgrave Macmillan | location = New York | isbn = 978-0-230-27866-0 | ref = harv}}\n* {{cite book | last = Vinogradov | first = V. K. | title = Hitler's Death: Russia's Last Great Secret from the Files of the KGB | publisher = Chaucer Press | year = 2005 | isbn = 978-1-904449-13-3 | ref = harv | url-access = registration | url = https://archive.org/details/hitlersdeathruss0000vino }}\n* Wistrich, Robert (1987). ''Wer war Wer im dritten Reich'' (Frankfurt am Main)\n* [http://www.dieterwunderlich.de/Goring_Goebbels.htm Dieter Wunderlich: G\u00f6ring und Goebbels] (Regensburg, 2002)\n\n== External links ==\n{{wikiquote}}\n{{Commons category|Magda Goebbels}}\n* [http://video.google.com/videoplay?docid=-8973962176504385280 Home movies of Magda and her children, summer 1942]\n\n{{Final occupants of the F\u00fchrerbunker}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Goebbels, Magda}}\n[[Category:1901 births]]\n[[Category:1945 deaths]]\n[[Category:German mass murderers]]\n[[Category:German murderers of children]]\n[[Category:Murderers who committed suicide]]\n[[Category:Female suicides]]\n[[Category:People from Berlin]]\n[[Category:German female murderers]]\n[[Category:Joint suicides by Nazis]]\n[[Category:Nazis who committed suicide by firearm in Germany]]\n[[Category:Filicides in Germany]]\n[[Category:Quandt family|Magda]]\n[[Category:Nazis who committed suicide in Berlin]]\n[[Category:Goebbels family|Magda]]\n[[Category:Women in Nazi Germany]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox First Lady\n| name = Magda Goebbels\n| image = Bundesarchiv Bild 183-R22014, Magda Goebbels.jpg\n| caption = Goebbels in 1933\n|birth_name=Johanna Maria Magdalena Ritschel\n| birth_date = {{birth date|1901|11|11|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Berlin]], [[German Empire]]\n| death_date = {{death date and age|df=yes|1945|5|1|1901|11|11}}\n| death_place = [[F\u00fchrerbunker]], Berlin, [[Nazi Germany]]\n| restingplace = \n| alma_mater = [[Ursuline Convent]] \n| profession = [[Propagandist]]\n| office1=\n| term_start1= \n| term_end1= \n| successor1= \n| party = [[National Socialist German Workers' Party]] (NSDAP)\n| spouse = {{plainlist |\n* {{marriage|[[G\u00fcnther Quandt]]|1921|1929|reason=divorced}}\n* {{marriage|[[Joseph Goebbels]]|1931|1945|reason=died}}\n }}\n| children = 7\n| awards =[[Golden Party Badge]] [[File:\u041f\u043b\u0430\u043d\u043a\u0430 \u0417\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0442\u043e\u0439 \u043f\u0430\u0440\u0442\u0438\u0439\u043d\u044b\u0439 \u0437\u043d\u0430\u043a \u041d\u0421\u0414\u0410\u041f.svg|50px]]<br>[[Cross of Honor of the German Mother]]\n|parents=Auguste Behrend<br>Oskar Ritschel}}\n\n'''Johanna Maria Magdalena''' \"'''Magda'''\" '''Goebbels''' ([[Married and maiden names|n\u00e9e]] '''Ritschel'''; 11 November 1901 \u2013 1 May 1945) was the wife of [[Nazi Germany]]'s Propaganda Minister [[Joseph Goebbels]]. A prominent member of the [[Nazi Party]], she was a close ally, companion and political supporter of [[Adolf Hitler]].<ref name=\"hisext\">{{cite web |last1=Wyllie |first1=James |title=Nazi wives: the women beside Hess, Goebbels, G\u00f6ring and Himmler |url=https://www.historyextra.com/period/20th-century/nazi-wives-women-who-ilse-hess-magda-goebbels-emmy-goring/ |website=HistoryExtra |publisher=BBC History Revealed |accessdate=11 February 2020 |date=February 2020}}</ref> Some historians refer to her as the unofficial \"[[First Lady]]\" of Nazi Germany, while others give that title to [[Emmy G\u00f6ring]].{{sfn|Thacker|2010|p=179}}{{sfn|Longerich|2015|pp=159, 160}}\n\nWith defeat imminent during the [[Battle of Berlin]] at the end of [[World War II]] in Europe, she and her husband murdered their [[Goebbels children|six children]] before committing [[suicide]] in the [[Reich Chancellery]] gardens. Her eldest son, [[Harald Quandt]], from a previous marriage, survived her.\n\n==Early life==\nMagda was born in 1901 in [[Berlin]], [[German Empire|Germany]] to unwed Auguste Behrend and building contractor and engineer, Oskar Ritschel.{{sfn|Longerich|2015|p=151}} The couple were married later that year and divorced in either 1904 or 1905.<ref name=dhm> [http://www.dhm.de/lemo/html/biografien/GoebbelsMagda/index.html Magda Goebbels biography] at Deutsches Historisches Museum, Berlin</ref>{{sfn|Longerich|2015|p=151}} Yet some sources suggest that the marriage was before Magda's birth, but there is no evidence to support such a prior wedding.<ref name=arditti>Arditti, Michael, [http://www.michaelarditti.com/non-fiction/magda goebbels-by-anja-klabunde/ ''Magda Goebbels'' by Anja Klabunde] Literary Review, 22 May 2002</ref>{{sfn|Meissner|1980|p=13}} When Magda was five, her mother sent her to [[Cologne]] to stay with her ex-husband.  In 1908, her mother married [[Richard Friedl\u00e4nder]], a wealthy Jewish merchant who worked in Brussels, who adopted Magda and whose surname she adopted.{{sfn|Longerich|2015|pp=151, 152}}  In Brussels, Magda was enrolled at the Ursuline Convent in [[Vilvoorde]]{{sfn|Meissner|1980|p=16}} where she was remembered as \"an active and intelligent little girl\".<ref>de Launay, Jaques, ''Hitler en Flandres'', 1975</ref>  During numerous visits to her father Ritschel, who lived in Duisburg and was a member of a Krefeld Masonic Lodge, Magda may have been introduced to Buddhism.<ref>{{cite web|title=Historie|periodical=|publisher=|url=http://www.freimaurer-krefeld.de/index.php/historie|url-status=|format=|access-date=|archive-url=|archive-date=|last=|date=|year=|language=|pages=|quote=}}</ref>\n\nIn 2016, it was reported that Friedl\u00e4nder may have been actually Magda's biological father, as stated in his residency card, discovered in Berlin archives by writer and historian [[Oliver Hilmes]].<ref name=\"thejc.com\"> [http://www.thejc.com/news/world-news/162206/magda-goebbels-biological-father-may-have-been-jewish Magda Goebbels' biological father may have been Jewish] Jewish Chronicle. 21 August 2016. Retrieved 22 August 2016.</ref>{{sfn|Meissner|1980|p=16}}{{sfn|Longerich|2015|pp=151, 152}} Hence, Magda's adoption upon her parents' delayed wedding may have been required merely to update the girls 'illegitimate child' status.<ref>Magda Goebbels, Gef\u00e4hrtin des B\u00f6sen In:  Der Spiegel Vol. 39, 24. September 2001 [http://www.spiegel.de/spiegel/print/d-20184307.html]</ref> \n\nFrom 1908 until the outbreak of [[World War I]], the family remained in Brussels. At that time, all Germans were forced to leave Belgium as refugees to avoid repercussions from the Belgian people after the German invasion.<ref name=\"dhm\" /> The family moved to Berlin where Magda attended the high school Kolmorgen Lyc\u00e9e. Behrend divorced Friedl\u00e4nder in 1914, and in 1919, Magda was enrolled in the prestigious Holzhausen Ladies' College near [[Goslar]].<ref name=\"dhm\" /> While in Berlin, Magda also befriended Lisa Arlosoroff and became intimate with her brother Haim, an ardent Zionist.{{sfn|Shindler|2017|pp=46\u201347}} During her relationship with Arlosoroff, she briefly wore a Star of David he had given her and even attended meetings of Tikvat Zion; the relationship did not last but the two remained in contact during the 1920s.{{sfn|Shindler|2017|p=47}}\n\n==Marriage and son with G\u00fcnther Quandt==\nIn 1920, while returning to school on a train, she met [[G\u00fcnther Quandt]], a rich German industrialist twice her age.{{sfn|Longerich|2015|p=152}} Thereafter, he courted her with courtesy and grand gestures.{{sfn|Meissner|1980|p=29}} He demanded that she change her surname back to Ritschel (having borne many years the surname of Friedl\u00e4nder), when converting from [[Catholicism]] to Quand's [[Protestantism|Protestant church]].{{sfn|Meissner|1980|p=31}} They were married on 4 January 1921, and her first child, [[Harald Quandt|their Harald]], was born on 1 November 1921.{{sfn|Thacker|2010|p=149}}\n\nMagda soon grew frustrated in her marriage because Quandt spent little time with her. His main interest seemed to be the expansion of his business empire.{{sfn|Longerich|2015|p=152}} She was left to look after six children - Harald, with Quandt's two sons from prior marriage, and three children from a deceased friend, then run the whole household.{{sfn|Longerich|2015|p=152}}\n\nIn October 1927, the couple went on a two month visit to the United States, to conduct a business with the Lloyd Electric Storage Battery Co. of  [[Philadelphia]].<ref>''List or Manifest of Alien Passengers For the United States Immigration Officer At the Port of Arrival'' (Form 500 U.S. Department of Labor, Immigration Service), pp. 7\u20138, number on list 3 & 4, dated October 22 & 28, 1927.</ref>  In 1929, Quandt discovered that Magda was having an affair, so they separated, then went on to divorce that same year, which terms were however quite generous with Magda.{{sfn|Longerich|2015|p=152}}\n\n==Marriage and family with Joseph Goebbels==\n[[File:Bundesarchiv Bild 183-R32860, Berlin, Trauung von Joseph und Magda Goebbels.jpg|left|thumb|Joseph and Magda's wedding day, with her son Harald Quandt in his [[Deutsches Jungvolk]] uniform. [[Adolf Hitler]], their [[best man]], can be seen in the background.]]\n\nIn 1930, Magda attended a meeting of the [[Nazi Party]] where she was impressed by one of the speakers, [[Joseph Goebbels]], then the [[Gauleiter]] of Berlin. She joined the party on 1 September 1930, and did some volunteer work, although she has not been characterized as politically active. From the local branch, Magda moved to the party headquarters in Berlin and for a brief period became secretary to Hans Meinshausen, Goebbels' deputy, before being invited to take charge of Goebbels' own private papers.{{sfn|Meissner|1980|p=82}} She and Goebbels became romantically involved while on a short trip with friends to Weimar in February 1931.{{sfn|Longerich|2015|p=152}} A relationship began and by April they began making plans for their future together.{{sfn|Longerich|2015|p=153}} Goebbels wrote in his diary, \"We have made a solemn vow to each other: When we have conquered the [[Reich]], we will become man and wife. I am very happy.\"{{sfn|Longerich|2015|p=153}} Her flat on [[Theodor-Heuss-Platz]] (then named the ''Reichskanzlerplatz'') soon became a favourite meeting place for [[Adolf Hitler]] and other NSDAP officials.{{sfn|Manvell|Fraenkel|2010|p=94}}\n\nBy September, the relationship was experiencing problems. Goebbels was often jealous, and had some concern over the fact that Hitler had grown fond of Magda.{{sfn|Longerich|2015|pp=153, 157, 158}} Magda decided to move forward their wedding date,{{sfn|Longerich|2015|p=153}} and the couple were married on 19 December 1931, with Hitler as a witness.{{sfn|Longerich|2015|p=167}}  [[Otto Wagener]] claims that Magda's marriage to Goebbels was somewhat arranged; since Hitler intended to remain unmarried, it was suggested that as the wife of a leading and highly visible Nazi official she might eventually act as \"first lady of the [[Third Reich]]\". Her social connections and upper class bearing may have influenced Goebbels' own enthusiasm.<ref name=wagener>Wagener, Otto, ''Hitler: Memoirs of a Confidant''</ref> Goebbels biographer [[Peter Longerich]] concurred with this \"plausible\" conclusion as Magda was a very ambitious woman.{{sfn|Longerich|2015|pp=159, 160}} Meissner contends that Hitler (though undoubtedly impressed by Magda) was an exceptionally close friend of the couple in the early days. Hitler enjoyed staying at the Goebbels' Berlin apartment, where he could relax,{{sfn|Longerich|2015|p=160}} and he grew very fond of the Goebbels' children.{{sfn|Longerich|2015|pp=159, 160}} Hitler would often arrive at their apartment late at night and, in later years, was as likely as Goebbels to sit with the baby Helga (born 1932) on his lap while they talked into the night.{{sfn|Meissner|1980|pp=91, 97\u201399}}\n[[File:Bundesarchiv Bild 146-1978-086-03, Joseph Goebbels mit Familie.jpg|thumb|The Goebbels family in 1942: (back row) Hildegard, [[Harald Quandt]], Helga; (front row) Helmut, Hedwig, Magda, Heidrun, [[Joseph Goebbels|Joseph]] and Holdine. (In this well-known [[manipulated image]],{{refneeded|date=April 2020}} the visage of the uniformed Harald, who was actually away on military duties, was inserted and retouched.)]]\n\nMagda had a close relationship with Hitler, and became a member of his small coterie of female friends.{{sfn|Manvell|Fraenkel|2010|p=94}} She acted as an unofficial representative of the regime, receiving letters from all over Germany from women with questions about domestic matters or child custody issues.{{sfn|Thacker|2010|p=179}}\n\nAfter 1933, the Goebbels family became accustomed to the luxurious lifestyle which went with their high social position. Their Berlin home on G\u00f6ringstrasse was remodeled by [[Albert Speer]] and they spent the spring and summers in Kladow.{{sfn|Longerich|2015|pp=231, 290\u2013291}} In 1936, they bought a villa on Schwanenwerder island and later another at Bogensee near Wandlitz in Brandenburg.{{sfn|Longerich|2015|pp=315, 316}}\n\n{{main|Goebbels children}}\nJoseph and Magda Goebbels had six children: Helga Susanne (1932), Hildegard \"Hilde\" Traudel (1934), Helmut Christian (1935), Holdine \"Holde\" Kathrin (1937), Hedwig \"Hedda\" Johanna (1938), and Heidrun \"Heide\" Elisabeth (1940).{{sfn|Manvell|Fraenkel|2010|p=165}}\n\n[[File:Bogensee 25.jpg|thumb|Goebbels' villa on Bogensee,<br>2008 condition]]\nJoseph Goebbels had many affairs during the marriage. In 1936, Goebbels met the [[Czech people|Czech]] actress [[L\u00edda Baarov\u00e1]] and by the winter of 1937 began an intense affair with her.{{sfn|Longerich|2015|pp=317, 318}} Magda had a long conversation with Hitler about the situation on 15 August 1938.{{sfn|Longerich|2015|p=392}} Unwilling to put up with a scandal involving one of his top ministers, Hitler demanded that Goebbels break off the relationship.{{sfn|Manvell|Fraenkel|2010|p=170}} Thereafter, Goebbels and Magda seemed to reach a truce until the end of September.{{sfn|Longerich|2015|p=392}} The couple had another falling out at that point, and once again Hitler became involved, insisting the couple stay together.{{sfn|Longerich|2015|pp=392\u2013395}} Hitler arranged for publicity photos to be taken of himself with the reconciled couple in October 1938.{{sfn|Longerich|2015|pp=391, 395}}{{efn|In 1939 at the premiere of the film ''[[The Journey to Tilsit]]'', Magda ostentatiously left because the plot had an accidental resemblance to her situation and the affair between her husband and Baarov\u00e1. {{harv|Romani|1994|p=86}}}} Magda also had affairs, including a relationship with [[Kurt Ludecke]] in 1933{{sfn|Longerich|2015|p=317}} and [[Karl Hanke]] in 1938.{{sfn|Thacker|2010|p=204}}\n\n==War years==\nAt the outbreak of war, Magda's son by her first marriage, Harald Quandt, became a [[Luftwaffe]] pilot and fought at the front, while, at home, she lived up to the image of a patriotic mother by training as a [[German Red Cross|Red Cross]] nurse and working with the electronics company [[Telefunken]], and travelled to work on a bus, like her colleagues.<ref name=\"arditti\" /> She was also involved with entertaining the wives of the foreign heads of state, supporting the troops and comforting war widows.\n\nBoth Goebbels and Magda derived personal benefits and social status from their close association with Hitler, and the couple remained loyal to Hitler and publicly supported him. Privately, however, Magda expressed doubts, especially after the war began to go badly on the [[Eastern Front (World War II)|Eastern Front]]. On 9 November 1942, during a gathering with friends listening to a speech by Hitler, she switched off the radio exclaiming, \"My God, what a lot of rubbish.\"{{sfn|Meissner|1980|p=219}} In 1944, she reportedly said of Hitler, \"He no longer listens to voices of reason. Those who tell him what he wants to hear are the only ones he believes.\"{{sfn|Meissner|1980|p=222}}  There is no evidence that Magda attempted to intervene to save her Jewish stepfather from the [[Holocaust]]. Though his fate has not been established, it is widely assumed that he perished in the camps. Asked about her husband's [[antisemitism]], she answered: \"The F\u00fchrer wants it thus, and Joseph must obey.\"{{sfn|Meissner|1980|p=127}}\n\nFelix Franks, a German Jew who later became a British soldier, claimed that his grandparents got an [[exit visa]] from Germany with the help of Magda Goebbels:{{quote|My father and step-mother were left behind in Germany but, two days before the War started, they were asked to come to Gestapo Headquarters and given an exit visa. There is a story in the family which goes back to the First World War when my step-grandparents were asked to give shelter to a young woman who\u2019d been displaced by the war in Belgium. Although she had a Jewish step-father, she eventually married Joseph Goebbels! My stepmother believes she may have acted as a sort of protecting hand and was involved with the exit visa. Certainly, the night before Kristallnacht, they got an anonymous phone call warning my father not to go home that evening but to go somewhere safe. My step-mother swore it was Magda Goebbels.\"<ref name=arditti/><ref>Jewish Museum Berlin, major exhibition \"Home and Exile, The Jewish Quarterly.</ref>}}\n\nAfflicted with a weak heart and \"delicate health\", Magda would have extended periods of illness.{{sfn|Longerich|2015|pp=197, 361, 362, 706}} Towards the end of the war, she is known to have also suffered from severe depression and [[trigeminal neuralgia]].<ref>Klabunde, Anja, ''Magda Goebbels'', p. 302</ref> This condition affects a nerve in the face, and although usually harmless is considered to cause intense pain and can be notoriously hard to treat.<ref>[http://www.tna-support.org/ What is Trigeminal Neuralgia?] TNA Website</ref> This often left her bedridden and led to bouts of hospitalization as late as August 1944.{{sfn|Meissner|1980|pp=141, 228, 234}}\n\n==Death==\nIn late April 1945, the Soviet [[Red Army]] entered Berlin, and the Goebbels family moved into the ''[[Vorbunker]]'', connected to the lower ''[[F\u00fchrerbunker]]'' under the [[Reich Chancellery]] garden.{{sfn|Thacker|2010|p=298}} Magda wrote a farewell letter to her son Harald, who was in a [[prisoner of war|POW]] camp in [[North Africa]]:<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://spartacus-educational.com/Magda_Goebbels.htm|title=Magda Goebbels|work=Spartacus Educational|access-date=2017-04-26|language=en}}</ref>{{quote|My beloved son! By now we have been in the F\u00fchrerbunker for six days already\u2014daddy, your six little siblings and I, for the sake of giving our national socialistic lives the only possible honourable end ... You shall know that I stayed here against daddy's will, and that even on last Sunday the F\u00fchrer wanted to help me to get out. You know your mother\u2014we have the same blood, for me there was no wavering. Our glorious idea is ruined and with it everything beautiful and marvelous that I have known in my life. The world that comes after the F\u00fchrer and national socialism is not any longer worth living in and therefore I took the children with me, for they are too good for the life that would follow, and a merciful God will understand me when I will give them the salvation ... The children are wonderful ... there never is a word of complaint nor crying. The impacts are shaking the bunker. The elder kids cover the younger ones, their presence is a blessing and they are making the F\u00fchrer smile once in a while. May God help that I have the strength to perform the last and hardest. We only have one goal left: loyalty to the F\u00fchrer even in death. Harald, my dear son\u2014I want to give you what I learned in life: be loyal! Loyal to yourself, loyal to the people and loyal to your country ... Be proud of us and try to keep us in dear memory ...}}\n\nGoebbels added a postscript to Hitler's [[Last will and testament of Adolf Hitler|last will and testament]] of 29 April stating that he would disobey the order to leave Berlin, \"[f]or reasons of humanity and personal loyalty\". Further, he stated that Magda and their children supported his refusal to leave Berlin and his resolution to die in the bunker. He later qualified this by stating that the children would support the decision [to commit suicide] if they were old enough to speak for themselves.{{sfn|Longerich|2015|p=686}}\n\nMagda was among the last to see both Hitler and [[Eva Braun]] before they [[Death of Adolf Hitler|committed suicide]] on the afternoon of 30 April.{{sfn|Kershaw|2001|pp=827\u2013828}} On the following day, 1&nbsp;May, Magda and Joseph arranged for SS dentist [[Helmut Kunz]] to inject [[Goebbels children|their six children]] with [[morphine]] so that when they were unconscious, an ampule of [[cyanide]] could be then crushed in each of their mouths. Kunz later stated he gave the children morphine injections, but it was Magda and SS-''[[Obersturmbannf\u00fchrer]]'' [[Ludwig Stumpfegger]] (Hitler's personal doctor) who administered the cyanide.{{sfn|Beevor|2002|pp=380, 381}} Author [[James P. O'Donnell]] concluded that although Stumpfegger was probably involved in drugging the children, Magda killed them herself. He surmises that witnesses blamed the deaths on Stumpfegger because he was a convenient target, having died the following day. Moreover, as O'Donnell states, Stumpfegger may have been too intoxicated at the time of the deaths to have played a reliable role.{{sfn|O'Donnell|2001}}\n\nMagda appears to have contemplated and talked about killing her children a month in advance.{{sfn|Meissner|1980|p=242}} According to her friend and sister-in-law (from her first marriage) Ello Quandt, she told her that they were all going to take poison.\n{{quote|We have demanded monstrous things from the German people, treated other nations with pitiless cruelty. For this the victors will exact their full revenge...we can't let them think we are cowards. Everybody else has the right to live. We haven't got this right\u2014we have forfeited it. I make myself responsible. I belonged. I believed in Hitler and for long enough in Joseph Goebbels...Suppose I remain alive, I should immediately be arrested and interrogated about Joseph. If I tell the truth I must reveal what sort of man he was\u2014must describe all that happened behind the scenes. Then any respectable person would turn from me in disgust. It would be equally impossible to do the opposite\u2014that is to defend what he has done, to justify him to his enemies, to speak up for him out of true conviction...That would go against my conscience. So you see, Ello, it would be quite impossible for me to go on living. We will take the children with us, they are too good, too lovely for the world which lies ahead. In the days to come Joseph will be regarded as one of the greatest criminals that Germany has ever produced. His children would hear that said daily, people would torment them, despise and humiliate them. They would have to bear the burden of his sins and vengeance would be wreaked on them... It has all happened before. You know how I told you at the time quite frankly what the F\u00fchrer said in the Caf\u00e9 Anast in Munich when he saw the little Jewish boy, you remember? That he would like to squash him flat like a bug on the wall...I couldn't believe it and thought it was just provocative talk. But he really did it later. It was all so unspeakably gruesome...<ref>Klabunde, Anja, ''Magda Goebbels''</ref><ref>\"Ello Quandt testimony\"</ref>}}\n\nShe appears to have refused several offers, such as one by [[Albert Speer]], to have the children smuggled out of Berlin and insisted that the family must stay at her husband's side. In the ''F\u00fchrerbunker'' she confided to Hitler's secretary [[Traudl Junge]], that \"I would rather have my children die, than live in disgrace, jeered at. My children stand no chance in Germany after the war\".<ref>Junge, Traudl, ''Until the Final Hour''</ref>\n\nThe last survivor of Hitler's bunker, [[Rochus Misch]], gave this account of the events to the [[BBC]]:\n\n{{quote|Straight after Hitler's death, Mrs. Goebbels came down to the bunker with her children. She started preparing to kill them. She couldn't have done that above ground\u2014there were other people there who would have stopped her. That's why she came downstairs\u2014because no-one else was allowed in the bunker. She came down on purpose to kill them.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/europe/8234018.stm | work=BBC News | title=I was in Hitler's suicide bunker | date=3 September 2009 | accessdate=12 May 2010}}</ref>}}\n\nShe helped the girls change into long white nightgowns. She then softly combed their hair. Misch tried to concentrate on his work but he knew what was going to happen.{{sfn|Misch|2014|p=176}} Magda then went back up to the ''Vorbunker'' with the children. Shortly thereafter, [[Werner Naumann]] came down to the ''F\u00fchrerbunker'' and told Misch that he had seen Hitler's personal physician, Dr Stumpfegger give the children something \"sweetened\" to drink.{{sfn|Misch|2014|p=177}} About two hours later, Magda came back down to the ''F\u00fchrerbunker'', alone. She looked very pale, her eyes very red and her face was \"frozen\". She sat down at a table and began playing [[Patience (game)|patience]].{{sfn|Misch|2014|p=177}} Goebbels then came over to her, but did not say a word at that time.{{sfn|Misch|2014|p=177}}\n\nAfter their children were dead, Magda and Joseph Goebbels walked up to the garden of the Chancellery, where they committed [[suicide]].{{sfn|Joachimsthaler|1999|p=52}} There are several different accounts of this event. One account was that they each bit on a cyanide ampule near where Hitler had been buried, and were given a [[coup de gr\u00e2ce]] immediately afterwards.{{sfn|Beevor|2002|p=381}} Goebbels' SS adjutant [[G\u00fcnther Schw\u00e4germann]] testified in 1948 that they walked ahead of him up the stairs and out into the Chancellery garden. He waited in the stairwell and heard the shots sound. Schw\u00e4germann then walked up the remaining stairs and, once outside, saw their lifeless bodies. Following Goebbels' prior order, Schw\u00e4germann had an SS soldier fire several shots into Goebbels' body, which did not move.{{sfn|Joachimsthaler|1999|p=52}}{{efn|[[Johannes Hentschel]] later told Misch a singular conflicting story that Goebbels killed himself in his room in the bunker, and Magda in the ''Vorbunker'', during the early hours of 2&nbsp;May. {{harv|Misch|2014|pp=182, 183}}}} The bodies were then doused with [[gasoline|petrol]], but the remains were only partially burned and not buried.{{sfn|Beevor|2002|p=381}}\n\nThe charred corpses were found on the afternoon of 2 May 1945 by Soviet troops. Magda's face was unrecognizable compared to that of her husband.{{sfn|Ryan|1994|p=366}} The children were found in the ''Vorbunker'' dressed in their nightclothes, with ribbons tied in the girls' hair.{{sfn|Beevor|2002|p=398}} The remains of the Goebbels' family, Hitler, Eva Braun, General [[Hans Krebs (Wehrmacht general)|Hans Krebs]], and [[Blondi|Hitler's dogs]] were repeatedly buried and exhumed.{{sfn|Vinogradov|2005|pp=111, 333}} The last burial was at the [[SMERSH]] facility in [[Magdeburg]] on 21 February 1946. In 1970, [[KGB]] director [[Yuri Andropov]] authorised an operation to destroy the remains.{{sfn|Vinogradov|2005|p=333}} On 4 April 1970, a Soviet KGB team used detailed burial charts to exhume five wooden boxes at the Magdeburg facility. The remains from the boxes were burned, crushed, and scattered into the Biederitz river, a tributary of the nearby [[Elbe]].{{sfn|Vinogradov|2005|pp=335, 336}}\n\n== Portrayal in media ==\nMagda Goebbels has been portrayed by the following actresses in film and television productions.<ref name=\"imdb\">{{cite web | url = https://www.imdb.com/character/ch0042561/ | title = Magda Goebbels (Character) | accessdate = 8 May 2008 | author = | last = | first = | authorlink = | coauthors = | date = | year = | month = | format = | work = | publisher = [[IMDb.com]] | pages = |